  "commentary": "With SPX at 6821.38 sitting just above the GEX flip at 6815 in a PIN regime, dealers are long gamma and will sell into strength as we approach the massive 6830 resistance wall (+148.6B GEX). The heavy concentration of positive gamma between 6820-6850 creates a strong ceiling effect, while the flip at 6815 acts as critical support - a break below flips dealers short gamma and removes the stabilizing bid.\n\nGiven the -7.2% drop over 5 minutes yet only 0.6% current change, we're seeing the PIN regime's mean reversion forces at work, but upside is capped by the monster gamma wall at 6830 where dealer selling pressure intensifies.\n\nKey levels: 6815 flip (support), 6830 max gamma wall (resistance), and 6770 negative gamma strike where dealer buying would kick in if we break the flip.\n\nBottom line: expect price to grind sideways between 6815-6830 with limited breakout potential.",
